# StreamList Project Rules (AI-First Development)

## 🔒 Core Architecture Rules

- Screens must NEVER contain data fetching logic.
- No useEffect + API calls inside screen components.
- All data fetching must be handled via custom hooks inside src/hooks/.

- All API calls must go through src/api/client.ts.
- Direct usage of axios in components or hooks is STRICTLY PROHIBITED.
- API functions must be defined in src/api/movies.ts and imported where needed.

## 🎨 Theming Rules

- No hardcoded color values are allowed anywhere in the codebase.
- All colors must be imported from src/theme/colors.ts.

- No hardcoded spacing values (e.g., margin: 10, padding: 16).
- All spacing must come from src/theme/spacing.ts.

- No inline font styles.
- Typography must come from src/theme/typography.ts.

## 🧩 Component Rules

- All components must be functional components using TypeScript.
- Use StyleSheet.create() for styling (no inline styles unless absolutely necessary).
- No use of any type — strict typing required.

## 🔄 State Management Rules

- Global state must be handled ONLY using Zustand.
- Redux, MobX, or any other state library is NOT allowed.

- Watchlist state must persist using AsyncStorage.
- Hydration must be handled before rendering dependent UI.

## 🌐 API & Environment Rules

- API tokens must NEVER be hardcoded.
- All environment variables must be accessed via @env (react-native-dotenv).
- .env file must NOT be committed to version control.
- .env.example must be present with placeholder values.

## 🧭 Navigation Rules

- Navigation must use React Navigation v6 ONLY.
- All navigation types must be defined in src/navigation/types.ts.
- No untyped navigation calls allowed.

## 📁 Folder Structure Rules

- Follow the exact folder structure defined in the project spec.
- Do not create unnecessary folders or files.
- Keep separation of concerns strictly enforced.

## ⚠️ Error & Loading Handling

- Every API-driven UI must handle:
  - Loading state (use skeleton loaders, NOT spinners)
  - Error state (with retry option)
  - Empty state (user-friendly UI)

## 🚫 Strictly Prohibited

- No hardcoded API keys
- No direct axios usage outside api/client.ts
- No CSS-in-JS libraries (Styled Components, NativeWind, etc.)
- No UI libraries (React Native Paper, Elements, etc.)
- No inline business logic inside UI components

## 🎯 AI Behavior Instructions

- Always follow the defined architecture before generating code.
- Prefer consistency over shortcuts.
- If unsure, default to modular and reusable patterns.
- Do not introduce new libraries unless explicitly asked.
- Always respect existing file structure and conventions.

## 🧠 Development Philosophy

- Prioritize clarity over cleverness
- Prefer simple, maintainable solutions
- Handle edge cases proactively
- Think beyond the spec when implementing features
